g.text: Visual Calculus: Is there something here that would indicate a sniper used this place as a nest for taking the shot? Just some urban detritus, a bottle and a dilapidated old comms tower.
You: Maybe the assailant climbed the comms tower, took the shot there?
"Maybe the assailant climbed the comms tower, took the shoot there?"
You: What about the cigarette butts?
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's not possible to climb that ladder and even if it were -- why? There's no platform up there to aim from." The lieutenant looks up, raising his collar.
Visual Calculus: The salty water has corroded the ladder to nothing but two thin orange rails. In addition, there is no stable nest up there. It would have been useless.
Kim Kitsuragi: "To warm his hands before pulling the trigger? Perhaps. But anyone could have made this. The coast is specked with fires this time of year." He looks around.

Visual Calculus: To warm his hands before he pulled the trigger? There are no markings on the ground for a tripod, he would have had to lie on a mattress. This is simply not a good spot for a 1.2 kilometre shot.
You: I want to know *a lot* more about this.
You: Enough. The cigarettes are unimportant.
Inland Empire: Still, you felt it was important enough to make a mental note. That means *something*. You didn't pay attention to any of the other cigarette butts on the coast.
You: "No what -- an orange pilot cap would not help?"
"No what -- a black pilot cap would not help?"
Rhetoric: How do you respond to a pithy *no* like that? He's just *not* into pilot caps, it seems.
You: "Copsicle. You meant to say copsicle."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No. I did not. We *Seolites* don't do paranomastic humour."
Esprit de Corps: Esprit de Corps: "..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Those?" He points to them. "A smoking assailant who favours Tioumoutiri to Astra or Drouin? Cigarette butts are everywhere. This is a common brand for old men."
Encyclopedia: Tioumoutiri was a Revacholian colony on Iilmaraa. The suzerainty's population was mostly Iilmaraan Areopagites -- up to 97%. The region was known for its tobacco export. Hence the name.
You: "You're right. I should look into this situation before I die of hypothermia."
Visual Calculus: The light is off on the third floor of the Whirling-in-Rags. The young woman is gone who knows where. Safe, closed off. Her form no longer moves behind the glass there...
You: Look over the water -- to the Whirling-in-Rags.

Kim Kitsuragi: "Truthfully -- this seems like a very poor choice to take a 1.2 kilometre rifle shot from. Visibility is awful, there's water vapour everywhere -- I think we can rule out... B double prime, was it?"
Electrochemistry: Smoking. Drinking. Being happy and elated. Without you -- because you're here, freezing in the wind, aren't you? Doing your *detective work*.
Visual Calculus: There, 1.2 kilometres over the cold water of the bay, through a thick snowstorm melting flake by flake in the waves you see the smallest rectangle, barely visible.
You: "Kim, you look cold -- maybe a thicker coat?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'm okay. You on the other hand -- look like you're about to turn into a popsicle."
"I'm okay. You on the other hand, yefreitor... you look like you're about to turn into a popsicle."
Electrochemistry: Such a good girl, you think.

Encyclopedia: Oh, you do! The butts you saw had a silhouette of a boy wearing a kofia hat -- a tobacco picker. This boy is the Tioumoutiri brand logo. Contemporary Revacholians prefer Drouin (a local blend from the southern islands) or Astra, a legendary cigarette from Graad. Tioumoutiri is favoured by older men who like its old fashioned paper filter tips, insane amount of tar and the sweet smells of colonialism and halva.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, an orange pilot cap would not help." He turns to face the sea.
Rhetoric: Technically speaking that would be a...
Visual Calculus: There, 1.2 kilometres over the cold water of the bay, blue from the distance and the air, you see the smallest rectangle, barely visible.
Endurance: The wind picks up. Fine sea foam lashes your face. It feels like needles. You can take it -- just raise your collar, detective.
You: "It's my style. Superstar cops don't wear parkas. They rock out."
You: "What if I *want* to be a popsicle?"
Visual Calculus: The light is off on the third floor of the Whirling-in-Rags. The young woman is gone, in Precinct 57. Safe, closed off. Her form no longer moves behind the glass there...
Kim Kitsuragi: "No, an orange pilot cap would not help." He turns to face the sea.
"No, a black pilot cap would not help." He turns to face the sea.
Endurance: He looks like he's cold out here at the tip of the coast. The jacket is warm, but not for this weather.
You: I said finish the god damn thought.[Leave.]
Visual Calculus: It's glowing in the dark night. The lights are on. Klaasje must be in there... looks like she's kept her promise not to go out at night anymore.
Visual Calculus: It's late. There is no light on the third floor of the Whirling-in-Rags. No shape moves behind it. Klaasje must be out on the town.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, that one. No to the orange pilot cap." He turns to face the sea.
"Yes, that one. No to the black pilot cap." He turns to face the sea.
You: "No what -- an orange pilot cap would not help?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, that one. No to the orange pilot cap." He turns to face the sea.
Perception: In the distance you can hear the breakers roar.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't see it, officer. I don't see a person take a shot here and hit something there..." He looks east, over the coast. "In the Whirling-in-Rags."
"I don't see it, lieutenant double-yefreitor. I don't see a person take a shot *here* and hit something there..." he looks east, over the coast. "In the Whirling-in-Rags."
You: "Kim, you look cold -- maybe a little pilot cap?
Savoir Faire: It does look *extremely* rickety. And wouldn't help much either.
Visual Calculus: Are you sure? You haven't ruled out the shot coming from here yet...
You: Maybe the campfire was used by the perpetrator?
"Maybe the campfire was used by the perpetrator?"
Visual Calculus: A smoking assailant who favours Tioumoutiri to Astra or Drouin? Cigarette butts are part of the campfire set -- they're also everywhere.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Absolute idiocy," he nods in acknowledgement of the idiocy on display.
Visual Calculus: A glowing light on the third floor of the Whirling-in-Rags. With binoculars you would see a young woman's shape move behind the glass, her limbs long and slender.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Don't be silly, no one wants to be a popsicle."
Visual Calculus: There, 1.2 kilometres over the wave-crossed bay, through heavy, dark grey curtains of rain you see the smallest rectangle, barely visible.
